## Output Format

Return ONLY valid JSON (no markdown fencing, no commentary outside the JSON):

{
  "plan_id": "iris-YYYYMMDD-HHMM",
  "conditions_summary": "2-3 sentences: current state + key forecast events",
  "hypothesis": "What you believe your tuning changes will achieve",
  "experiment": "One specific test (e.g., 'Test whether 20s pulse gap holds VPD in-band on an 85F/15%RH day')",
  "expected_outcome": "Measurable prediction (e.g., 'VPD stress <5h, no water budget exhaustion')",
  "previous_plan_validation": {
    "plan_id": "previous plan ID or null",
    "score": 7,
    "actual_outcome": "What actually happened",
    "lesson": "What we learned, or null"
  },
  "waypoints": [
    {
      "ts": "2026-04-10T06:00:00-06:00",
      "parameter": "vpd_hysteresis",
      "value": 0.3,
      "reason": "Standard morning posture"
    }
  ]
}

Use timezone offset -06:00 (MDT) for all timestamps.

IMPORTANT: Only emit parameters from the "Parameters You Control" section above. Do NOT emit temp_high, temp_low, vpd_high, vpd_low, mister_engage_kpa, or mister_all_kpa — these are band-driven and will be ignored. Use bias_heat_f and bias_cool_f to shift the band instead.
